post_text:
A message from KCHS concerning Pep rallies:

Out of concern for the safety and well-being of students and staff, we regrettably notify you that pep rallies for the high school will not be open to the public. Please understand that this decision was not made in haste and input from the high school faculty and staff was solicited prior to making this decision. We will work with our technology department and audio visual production teacher to see if we can live stream the pep rally. Thank you for your understanding.

post_text:
Badger Football Fans, please read this information regarding Friday's scrimmage in Hondo.

Hondo is asking for only the immediate family of the players from Karnes City to attend the scrimmage. Before entering there will be a QR code to scan and answer questions, along with temperatures being taken. KC Family Fans will enter on the visitor side of the stadium.

KC JV Family Fans will be allowed to enter beginning at 5:00 PM. Upon conclusion of the JV scrimmage, the stands will be cleared for the KC Varsity Family Fans. Varsity Family Fans should not enter the stadium until 6:40 PM.

Admission will not be charged, but Honda is participating in the "Our Day to Shine" campaign and will be taking donations for the Texas High School Coaches Education Foundation (THSCEF) Benevolence Fund.

#WeWillBeChampions
#itsagreatdaytobeabadger
#BadgerPrideNeverDies

Attention KC Jr. High Girls' Athletics:

Cross Country Practice will be Monday through Friday (8/17-8/21) at 6:15 am; meet at the track.

Volleyball Practice will be Monday (8/17) at 7:00 am; please be sure to arrive between 6:45 am and 6:55 am at the high school gym. Coach Ramos will announce the rest of the practices for the week on Monday.

If you are not participating in a sport right now, please continue to report to the Jr. High front office by 7:45 am and then go to the new high school gym. We will get in roll call lines and take attendance when the bell rings.

Please continue to check your blackboard and our athletics google classroom for updates, announcements, and information.

Karnes City ISD
August 7 at 8:27 PM ·

2020-2021 KCISD Registration will remain open for any parents still needing to register.

If you are not able to register over the weekend, Monday, August 10th, you may come to the KCISD Boardroom beginning at 7:30 AM -3:00 PM to register your child on the computer. In order to limit the visitors to campus, please DO NOT go to the campus to register. Enter the boardroom by the KCISD Performing Arts Center.

There will be staff available to help. Social distancing and masks will be required, and a limited number of people will be allowed in the room to register at one time.

**Please share**

Meet the Badgers Night

We are very excited to start our 2020-2021 school year. KCISD will host two informational sessions regarding our school reopening plans. These sessions will be available face-to-face and over Zoom.

Meeting times will be this Wednesday, July 22nd at 6:00 PM and Thursday, July 23rd at 10:00 AM.

If attending face-to-face, the sessions will be held in the KCISD Performing Arts Center. Social distancing and local guidelines will be followed.

If attending through Zoom, the link to the Zoom meeting will be posted 1 hour before each session.

There will be a translator available for each session.

Para prevenir la propagación de COVID-19 en nuestra comunidad, practique el distanciamiento social:
• Evite salir en público
• Cuando esté en público, mantenga una distancia de seis pies entre usted y los demás.
• Seguir las recomendaciones de los funcionarios locales y estatales.
Obtenga más información en https://texas.gov/covid19
# covid19 #texasfuerte #quedateencasa

However, students who are enrolled in Dual Credit classes through Coastal Bend Community College, your deadlines will be decided by your professors through Coastal Bend, please continue to check your class site through Blackboard.

post_text: AV production’s 2020 UIL film submission has advanced to the semi-final round of the UIL Young Filmmaker’s competition. The film will be going up against 135 other films for a spot at the film state finals. Finals will be held at the Paramount Theater in Austin, Texas on February 25th, 2020. The film has also been nominated for the Nobelity Project Award. The nomination goes toward films that tackle global, society, or cultural issues.

post_text:
The Karnes City High School Twirlers competed at UIL Twirling Solo & Ensemble contest at Cuero High School on Saturday, February 1, 2020. Junior, Kelsey Janysek and Senior, Madyson Wiatrek earned a one on their solo and will have a chance to compete at state later this year. Freshman, Tiffany Janecek earned a one rating in a class three solo. The class one trio also earned a one rating and will advance to state competition later this year.

Congratulations to these young ladies!

RES Students are enjoying a sidewalk chalk party at school today for having perfect attendance the first nine weeks of school. Leading research indicates that being absent more than 10% of the school year, about 18 days, can have detrimental effects on a student's academic achievement. If your child is struggling with school attendance, please contact your child's teacher, school counselor or principal for a conference.

post_text: On Thursday, October 24th, KCHS will be having off-campus lunch. Students qualify for off-campus by earning A or A/B honor roll or perfect attendance and by receiving no discipline referrals and less than 5 tardies for the first nine weeks. Passes will be handed out to qualifying students during second period on Thursday. Students must have an off-campus consent form signed by a parent on file. Lunch will be from 12:12 to 1:12.

Parent Information:
San Antonio Cole Junior High and High School football games information

Gate procedures:

All adults in a vehicle will need to provide a license or photo ID.
Vehicle registration stickers will need to be current.
They will not allow vehicles on the base if they have an expired sticker. NO EXCEPTIONS!

The Winans Rd gate is the only entrance that has access to the school. After the game the gate to leave from Winans will close at 11:00 pm. Please let parents and fans know so they don’t get stuck having to leave through the main post. If the game goes late or is delayed, we will make adjustments to keep the gate open.

post_text: Before school on Wednesday, Sept 11, 2019 at Karnes City Primary School, for "First Responders Day", the following departments greeted the young students arriving on campus: KC Volunteer Fire Department, KC Police Department, Karnes County Sheriff's Office, Dept. of Public Safety, and KC Emergency Services (EMS). The students made and presented banners to show their gratitude to these community helpers!
